## Diagnosis

The nav logo text "Yilan Gao" is wrapping to two lines under viewport pressure because the flex container is distributing squeeze proportionally across all children, with no explicit instruction to treat the logo as a non-negotiable fixed element. The identity blurb is also likely `flex-shrink: 1` by default, meaning both items compete equally for space — and the logo loses because "Yilan Gao" is a shorter word-boundary candidate for the browser's line-break algorithm.

**Root cause:** Missing `whitespace-nowrap` + `flex-shrink-0` on the logo element, and no codified priority rule distinguishing identity-critical text from secondary content. This is **AP-072** (Unconstrained flex children without explicit shrink hierarchy) combined with a missing design token contract for core identity elements.

---

## Fix

### 1. `components/nav/NavLogo.tsx` (or wherever the logo renders)

```tsx
// Before — vulnerable to wrapping
<span className="font-bold text-lg">
  Yilan Gao
</span>

// After — identity-locked
<span
  className="font-bold text-lg whitespace-nowrap shrink-0"
  // shrink-0  → flex-shrink: 0  — refuses to give up space under any pressure
  // whitespace-nowrap → single atomic line, always
>
  Yilan Gao
</span>
```

---

### 2. `components/nav/Nav.tsx` — set the explicit shrink hierarchy on the flex container

```tsx
// Before
<nav className="flex items-center gap-4 px-6 py-4">
  <NavLogo />
  <NavBlurb />          {/* "Designer, AI systems experience..." */}
  <NavLinks />
</nav>

// After — explicit priority contract on every direct child
<nav className="flex items-center gap-4 px-6 py-4 min-w-0">

  {/* PRIORITY 0 — never moves, never wraps, never compromises */}
  <NavLogo />           {/* carries shrink-0 whitespace-nowrap internally */}

  {/* PRIORITY 1 — may wrap internally but never displaces logo */}
  <NavBlurb className="shrink min-w-0" />   {/* shrink=flex-shrink:1, min-w-0 allows truncation */}

  {/* PRIORITY 2 — collapses/hides at breakpoints per existing responsive rules */}
  <NavLinks className="shrink-0 ml-auto" />

</nav>
```

---

### 3. `components/nav/NavBlurb.tsx` — accept and apply the passed className

```tsx
interface NavBlurbProps {
  className?: string;
}

export function NavBlurb({ className }: NavBlurbProps) {
  return (
    <p
      className={cn(
        "text-sm text-muted-foreground",
        // min-w-0 is critical: without it, a flex child won't shrink
        // below its content's intrinsic width even with flex-shrink:1
        "min-w-0",
        className
      )}
    >
      Designer, AI systems experience&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;interfaces.
    </p>
  );
}
```

---

### 4. Codify the rule — `styles/identity.css` (new file, imported in global CSS)

```css
/**
 * IDENTITY PRIORITY SYSTEM
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * Core identity elements (logo, wordmark, name) are NEVER sacrificed
 * under layout pressure. They are the last thing that moves and the
 * first thing that is protected.
 *
 * Priority hierarchy when horizontal space is constrained:
 *
 *   P0 — IDENTITY-LOCKED   Never wraps. Never collapses. Never moves.
 *                           flex-shrink: 0; white-space: nowrap;
 *                           Examples: site logo, "Yilan Gao" wordmark
 *
 *   P1 — COMPRESSIBLE       May reflow internally (2-line ok).
 *                           flex-shrink: 1; min-width: 0;
 *                           Examples: tagline, identity blurb
 *
 *   P2 — COLLAPSIBLE        May hide at breakpoints.
 *                           Examples: nav links, secondary CTAs
 */

/* Utility: apply to any element that must never wrap */
.identity-locked {
  white-space: nowrap;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* Utility: apply to secondary copy that absorbs squeeze gracefully */
.identity-compressible {
  flex-shrink: 1;
  min-width: 0;
}
```

Then in `globals.css`:

```css
@import "./styles/identity.css";
```

---

### 5. Extend Tailwind config to expose these as semantic utilities — `tailwind.config.ts`

```ts
import type { Config } from "tailwindcss";

export default {
  theme: { /* ... */ },
  plugins: [
    // Codified identity priority as first-class utilities
    function ({ addUtilities }: { addUtilities: Function }) {
      addUtilities({
        ".identity-locked": {
          "white-space": "nowrap",
          "flex-shrink": "0",
        },
        ".identity-compressible": {
          "flex-shrink": "1",
          "min-width": "0",
        },
      });
    },
  ],
} satisfies Config;
```

Now in any component you write `identity-locked` and the rule is self-documenting and enforced by the design system — not by tribal knowledge.

---

## Principle

**A site's name is not content — it is infrastructure.** It occupies space before anything else does, at every viewport width, unconditionally. Secondary copy (taglines, blurbs) absorbs pressure gracefully *because* the identity element refuses to. The correct model is: identity elements declare `flex-shrink: 0` and `white-space: nowrap` at the component level so no parent can ever accidentally override the contract. This is codified here as the **P0/P1/P2 identity priority system** and should be treated as a load-bearing design token, not a CSS detail.
